  ],
  "final_text": "I'll read SPI1 and both DMA controllers in parallel to get the full picture at once.\n**No \u2014 DMA is not configured or armed for SPI1 RX.** Here's the full picture from the live register state:\n\n---\n\n### SPI1 side\n\n| Register | Field | Value | Meaning |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `CR2` | `RXDMAEN` | **0** | SPI1 is **not** issuing DMA requests on RX |\n| `CR2` | `TXDMAEN` | 0 | TX DMA also off |\n| `CR1` | `SPE` | 0 | SPI1 itself is disabled |\n| `SR` | `BSY/RXNE` | 0 | No activity |\n\n---\n\n### DMA1 side (SPI1 RX maps to DMA1 Ch2 on L476)\n\n| Register | Field | Value | Meaning |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `CCR2` | `EN` | **0** | Channel 2 **not enabled** |\n| `CCR2` | `DIR` | 0 | Direction would be peripheral\u2192memory (correct for RX), but irrelevant |\n| `CNDTR2` | `NDT` | **0** | No transfer count loaded |\n| `CPAR2` | `PA` | **0x00000000** | Peripheral address not set |\n| `CMAR2` | `MA` | **0x00000000** | Memory address not set |\n| `CSELR` | `C2S` | **0** | Channel 2 request selector = 0 (not mapped to SPI1 RX = `0x1`) |\n\n### DMA2\nDMA2 has no register state (all empty) \u2014 not involved.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThree things would all need to be true for DMA RX to be ready; **all three are false:**\n\n1. \u274c `SPI1->CR2.RXDMAEN` = 0 \u2014 SPI1 is not raising DMA requests\n2. \u274c `DMA1->CSELR.C2S` = 0 (needs `0x1` for SPI1\\_RX) \u2014 request routing not wired\n3. \u274c `DMA1->CCR2.EN` = 0 and `CNDTR2.NDT` = 0 \u2014 channel not armed, no transfer count, no addresses\n\nThe DMA/SPI1 path is completely unconfigured from reset state."
}